arts.ttl: Ruben Selles left with mixed emotions after Hull City's draw with Norwich City
arts.sum: The Canaries hit the post in the second half through Championship top scorer Bojra Sainz, with the hosts riding their luck, but held on to earn what could be a valuable point in their quest to avoid the drop, and Selles felt a share of the spoils was probably about fair. "That goal early in the second half probably cost us 5-10 minutes just to restart again, but I think after that we managed the game.

arts.ttl: Hull City's home struggles continue despite battling display against Norwich City
arts.sum: City tried to regroup and skipper Shane Duffy was booked as Crooks broke through the centre of the park before Selles made his first change just before the hour when Mason Burstow replaced Louie Barry after an enterprising debut, and shortly after the new arrival fired wide, Norwich brought on Lewis Dobbin for Jurasek. A lovely McLoughlin ball played in Barry down the left moments later, and his cut-back found Alzate running onto it, and he fired well wide from 20 yards out, and then Gelhardt angled a tame curling effort straight at Gunn in what was an encouraging opening and that promising start was rewarded with a deserved lead after 14 minutes.

arts.ttl: Hull City player ratings vs Norwich City as Tigers earn valuable point
arts.sum: City's promising start was rewarded inside the opening 15 minutes when a fine move was finished off by Matt Crooks who arrived to turn in Lewie Coyle's near post cross. Joao Pedro: Became increasingly isolated as the first half wore on and slipped deeper as the Tigers struggled to control the game, and in the much more even second period, they couldn't get him into the game.

arts.sum: Sargent’s 47th-minute goal was the third time that he has struck against the Tigers recently.

arts.ttl: Hull City crave a piece of Louie Barry 'magic' in quest to earn Championship survival
arts.sum: Hull City will be looking towards Louie Barry to carve out a piece of magic and aid their hopes of avoiding a demoralising relegation to League One. The youngster, who set League One alight in the first half of the season with 15 goals and three assists in 25 games for Stockport County, has yet to make an impact in the Championship in his 66 minutes thus far, but will be eyeing a first start against Norwich City on Saturday afternoon, as Ruben Selles' side look for a first home win of 2025 and just a third all season.

arts.ttl: Hull City January arrival adopts different approach in quest to solve MKM Stadium problems
arts.sum: If Ruben Selles' Tigers are to drag themselves out of danger, then winning some games at home will be crucial, especially with fellow strugglers Luton Town, Plymouth Argyle and Derby County to come in front of their long-suffering supporters and Joseph, who was one of eight new arrivals in the winter window, says the players can't change what's happened in the past, but can control their own destiny in the final 15 games. New Hull City signing Kyle Joseph says the Tigers dressing room must adopt a clean slate mentality in a bid to find some form in front of their own supporters.
